              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">MicroStrategy’s $42B fund raise</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-6-1.jpg" alt="MicroStrategy’s $42B fund raise" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">MicroStrategy, led by Michael Saylor, is <a href="https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/hedge-funds-microstrategy-wall-street-144245688.html" target="_blank">doubling down</a> on Bitcoin, raising $42 billion in capital through equity and convertible bonds. Hedge funds are jumping on the convertible arbitrage opportunities created by the company’s volatile stock, which has surged over 500% this year. These convertible notes allow funds to profit from wild price swings tied to Bitcoin. However, critics warn of risks if the crypto rally reverses. Saylor continues to use MicroStrategy as a bridge between traditional finance and crypto markets, raising questions about the long-term sustainability of this high-stakes strategy.</p>
        </mj-text>
