              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Private equity offloads energy assets</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-6-2.jpg" alt="Private equity offloads energy assets" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          Private equity firms are turning to continuation funds to <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/12/05/baupost-elliott-bet-big-on-private-equitys-aging-energy-assets/" target="_blank">offload</a> aging energy assets with Baupost Group and Elliott Management leading deals. These funds extend ownership of hard-to-sell oil and gas properties, allowing investors to negotiate discounts while injecting fresh capital. Despite high interest rates and ESG concerns, opportunistic investors see potential in these volatile assets. With hopes of regulatory changes under Trump’s administration and cheaper debt financing, private equity players expect a rebound in the energy sector's M&A activity.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
