              margin-top: 2px !important;">Berkshire Hathaway's cash pile reaches record $325 billion</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.altdaily.co/email/images/an-dec-6-3.jpg" alt="Berkshire Hathaway's cash pile reaches record $325 billion" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          Berkshire Hathaway, led by Warren Buffett, has amassed a staggering $325 billion in cash and cash equivalents, the highest in its history. This comes after selling $36 billion in stock holdings during Q3 2024, including a significant reduction in its Apple stake for the fourth consecutive quarter. The immense cash reserve underscores Buffett’s cautious outlook on current investment opportunities, favoring cash and U.S. Treasuries over equities.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px);">To put this cash hoard into perspective, it surpasses the market valuations of companies like Starbucks ($112 billion) and Target ($69 billion) and could theoretically acquire all 32 NFL teams at a 50% premium to their collective value.</p>
          
        </mj-text>
